  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bc1\u0bb5 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Request for military protection again",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kapila Natunna, joint secretary of the Petroleum Users Association, said that they are requesting the government to restore the military security removed from the petrol stations.",
        "He said that the reason for the removal of military security is not known, and if the soldiers who were on duty at the fuel stations are redeployed, the security of the fuel stations will be ensured.",
        "It is noteworthy that more than 13 people who were involved in chaos at fuel filling stations have been arrested in recent days. (a)"
      ],
